{
  "rule": "divergence_arakawa_c",
  "applicable": false,
  "skip_reason": "divergence_arakawa_c is a 2D rule on an Arakawa C-grid: it samples a vector field at face_x and face_y stagger positions and emits a scalar at cell_center. The current ESS verify_mms_convergence harness is wired only for 1D periodic Cartesian stencils whose selectors carry an integer `offset` keyed off `cell_center` sampling (see EarthSciSerialization src/mms_evaluator.jl: apply_stencil_periodic_1d). It cannot interpret the `arakawa` selector kind, the categorical `stagger` field, or the two-component `applies_to: {op: div, args: [$F]}` shape required here. A divergence-free MMS sweep — e.g. F(x,y) = (sin(2πy), -sin(2πx)) on the unit square (∇·F ≡ 0) — is the natural Layer-B target and is captured by a follow-up bead extending ESS to support 2D staggered MMS. This fixture exists so the walker reports a structured SKIP rather than a missing-fixture FAIL."
}
